T1  - Equilibrium policy in an overlapping generations economy
AU  - Loewy, Michael B.
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 22
IS  - 3
SP  - 485
EP  - 499
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/01/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(88)90010-4
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393288900104
AB  - This paper offers a mechanism for reducing the number of stationary equilibria that arise in a simple two-period-lived overlapping generations economy. Since each equilibrium is associated with a different combination of monetary and fiscal policies, I assume that at each date the agent in his second period of life determines how that period's monetary and fiscal instruments will be set. I show that the set of stationary equilibria where this occurs is a proper and nonempty subset of the set of stationary competitive equilibria and that at least one such equilibrium is a Pareto optimum.
ER  - 

